#10204
High upon Mount Olympus~
You stand upon a dark cloud, quite thin, yet terra firma nonetheless.
Random spots of light flash through the ground, what must be lightning striking
the world below, which you can see far off to the distance in the empty space,
only filled by small spots far away, the stars occupying the sky.  Your own
form is non existent, light seems to travel through you and everything else
here, no mass seems to have physical matter to it.  A prismed gate stands
here before you.  It too seems to be in a state without true form.  To pass
into it would take strength unknown to most mortals, though undoubtly what lies
beyond it may be heaven itself.
~
~
